# Frontend Rules

LotSync is mobile-first for lot operations. Pairing happens on phones; dashboard is for monitoring.

## Apps

| App | Stack | Role |
|-----|-------|------|
| `apps/web` | Next.js, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, TanStack Query | Dashboard, admin, interim pairing PWA |
| `apps/mobile` | React Native / Expo (future) | Primary pairing & lot ops UX |
| `packages/types` | TypeScript | Shared API types |
| `packages/api-client` | TypeScript | Shared HTTP client |
| `packages/ui` | React / RN | Shared primitives where overlap exists |

Do not scaffold `apps/mobile` until Milestone 4 pairing APIs are validated.

## Shared API Layer

- All clients call `apps/api` at `/api/v1`
- Use `packages/api-client` once created; never duplicate business logic in clients
- Auth via Supabase Bearer token — not cookie-only patterns

## Web Dashboard (`apps/web`)

- Desktop/tablet-first layout for inventory tables, sync monitoring, settings
- White-label as LotSync; never expose Minew or vendor branding

## Lot Operations UI

- Touch-first, large tap targets, minimal steps
- Pairing flow: scan VIN → scan ESL → confirm → pair
- Interim: responsive PWA in `apps/web` (M5)
- Production: native `apps/mobile` with Expo camera scanning

## UI Patterns

Every screen needs: loading state, empty state, error state.
Connect via `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` (web) or shared api-client (mobile).

## Security

- Clients never send arbitrary `dealership_id` for access control
- No provider API credentials in client code
